<br>
Well I finished the quest and I am only Level 21.... was 22 when I started so you know what happened <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Anyway I would like to say that it is not as hard as it seems.  Only thing is a lot of travel and gate spells a plus.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp In Erud's Crossing I saw the undead ship and the rod was a ways away from it.  Invis OK here and I did not see any sharks at all.  Nobody was camping them but may have been recently killed.  That Rod was very easily obtained.  <br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Everfrost underwater river to caves to house was OK but once at the house I underestimated the power of iced bone skellies.  3 of them conned green at 21.  They are casters however and I died 2 times trying.  3rd time I had help from a 40 shaman and a 40 some magician.  I only needed one of them though.  In these caves beware of the Lich and his pet.  They wander around and didn't ever come up to the house but on your way there you may run into them.  And yes endure breath will be needed.  Grab waterstones from a mage.  When you touch the rod all 3 get pissed and attack.  Never tried invis vs undead.  May be the key.  Found &quot;dusty old jawbone&quot; no doubt some other quest.<br>
<br>
Lake Rathe underwater cave to goblin tower much like the one in Oasis except more water travel and yes endure breath will be needed.  Invisible DOES work.  They never saw me they conned red and look threateningly.  There was also an npc named &quot;Deep&quot; with 3 gobs where rod was.  While invis you grab the rod, equip it and move along.<br>
<br>
Dagnor's Cauldron/Kedge Keep, I felt that you should really express in your description for this one that it is underwater.  I was unfamiliar with this area and found out it was in middle of lake underwater.  Endure breath might be avoidable with high level swim but recommended since it is dark and you might have a hard time seeing.  Swim around up top to find loc and then go down to grab.  Nobody guarding it for me.<br>
<br>
Lower Guk Dead Side Reanimated Hand Room, by far the HARDEST rod to obtain.  Getting to this zone is bad enough but then once in you need to go down to 3rd level and then to the D area (kinda like the 4th level (look at eqatlas.com's map for this area)).  There is somewhat of a safe area between 3rd level and the D area which is a hallway where ppl rest up.  There are corpses along here though no doubt from trains.  I had the luck of some guy there who checked out the way to the hand room and said there was nobody in it.  So he escorted me and you get to a room where you climb up a ramp and then there is water above you (gravity has no place here for water I guess) then you swim up.  The room up there is hand room and the Rod was there with no mobs (I most likely got lucky).  But I died 3 times doing this one.  All 3 times on 1st level not knowing I had to go down that far.  Invis vs Undead a MUST!!.  There are bats and maybe a type of froglok here that can see you with invis vs undead but hopefully they will be dead from groups killing them.  They are only on 1st level from what I saw.<br>
<br>
Oasis area is another underwater watergoblin tower thing.  Invis should suffice and endure breath not needed.<br>
<br>
Highpass Hold, other than being KOS in this town I had no problems finding/obtaining it.<br>
<br>
Qeynos Aquaducts/Catacombs, No problems obtaining.  Sharks there are usually camped.  NPC there liked me but killing him will help you with faction of Qeynos merchants and guards but make corrupt guards hate you.  NPC conned blue at 21.  Easy way there is to go to North Qeynos and get in that hidden area (looks like vines growing up a stone wall rest of wall has no vines).<br>
<br>
I told you about Neriak, it is in 2nd zone in from 1st zone.  There was a leatherfoot deputy swimming around it, and beside rod was some old coin for some other quest.<br>
<br>
Unrest had me scared esp since the whole guk thing.  It was a breeze.  I had the extra luck of getting a druid to group me and turn me into a wolf.  Undead do not aggro on wolves.  Invis vs undead would have sufficed.  Like it says water to the right of mansion, swim down go in hole cross corner form the one to spelunker.<br>
<br>
Took 3 nights (3-4 hour sessions).<br>
<br>
<br>
